{"type":"step-attempt","step":"design","sessionId":"f2c5b6ce-b73b-4af4-a799-99fcdd5fba0c","outcome":{"verdict":"success","findingsPath":null,"error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"reason":"Wrote design.md, spec.md, tasks.md under specrunner/changes/assurance-profile-spine/ for the R1 assurance-profile spine (feature). Plan mirrors the existing pipelineId pattern: EffectiveProfile type + self-consistent STANDARD_PROFILE (policyDigest derived at construction via computePolicyDigest, which hashes all fields EXCEPT policyDigest), JobState.profile?: EffectiveProfile, getProfile/computePolicyDigest helpers, buildInitialJobState default, immutable-per-job (spread preservation + compile-time patch Omit tooth), and fail-closed attach self-consistency verification in verifyCheckpoint (profile-inconsistent / profile-uninterpretable) with absent→standard backward compat.\n\nKey design finding surfaced during verification: the request's literal instruction to compute digests in src/state/profile.ts using hashObject from src/core/agent/hash.ts would create a shared-kernel→domain (B-3) layering divergence (architecture/model.md §3), tripping core-invariants.test.ts. Resolved via D1: relocate the dependency-free canonicalJson/hashObject to src/util/hash.ts (leaf) with a re-export shim at the old path (behavior-preserving, no consumer churn), so state can compute digests without a boundary violation. Also confirmed buildInitialJobState is the sole initial-state factory and that verifyCheckpoint routes through validateJobState, so validateJobState must stay lenient on profile to preserve the correct attach reason codes.\n\nOnly the three planning files were written; no source/README edits (PLAN-only, per override). All acceptance criteria are mapped to Requirements/Scenarios (spec.md) and tasks T-01..T-08 with acceptance criteria.","status":"success"},"followUpAttempts":0,"transientRetryAttempts":0,"addedTurns":{"reportRetry":0,"postWork":0,"outputRepair":0}},"startedAt":"2026-07-16T0